For some repositories you need to install keys first.
How to do this is in this file.
Some repositories require also apt-transport-https.

* deb-multimedia
wget https://www.deb-multimedia.org/pool/main/d/deb-multimedia-keyring/deb-multimedia-keyring_2016.8.1_all.deb
sudo gdebi deb-multimedia-keyring_2016.8.1_all.deb

* docker
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/debian/gpg | sudo apt-key add -

* dropbox
sudo apt-key adv --keyserver pgp.mit.edu --recv-keys 1C61A2656FB57B7E4DE0F4C1FC918B335044912E

* google 
wget -q -O - https://dl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub | sudo apt-key add -

* nodesource
curl --silent https://deb.nodesource.com/gpgkey/nodesource.gpg.key | sudo apt-key add -

* opera
wget -qO- https://deb.opera.com/archive.key | sudo apt-key add -

* skype
curl https://repo.skype.com/data/SKYPE-GPG-KEY | sudo apt-key add - 

* suldr
wget http://www.bchemnet.com/suldr/pool/debian/extra/su/suldr-keyring_2_all.deb
sudo gdebi suldr-keyring_2_all.deb

* teamviewer
wget -O - https://download.teamviewer.com/download/linux/signature/TeamViewer2017.asc | apt-key add -
